MassLogProcess
-------------

For the lattest information on this project: http://github.com/fygrave/masslogprocess
wiki page available at: http://wiki.github.com/fygrave/masslogprocess/

 Background History 
-------------------
MassLogProcess is a a framework for high performance system log processing. This is a fork of original 
masslogprocess available at https://masslogprocess.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/masslogprocess/

The main info site of original project is: http://www.secservice.net/bbs/viewforum.php?f=19
Some additional information available here: http://code.google.com/p/masslogprocess/
The project seems stale since 2009 so we forked out a branch. If you're author of the project, please get in touch, we'd be interested to merge some patches back.


How to check out the project
----------------------------

git clone git://github.com/fygrave/masslogprocess.git

Building the project
--------------------

You can build the project with Ant:

cd masslogprocess/JMLP
ant

Running the project
-------------------

You can run main project in server and "display" mode. 

The simplest way to start it is: java -classpath ./libs/OROMatcher1.0.jar;./libs/jppf-client.jar;./libs/jppf-common.jar;./libs/jppf-common-node.jar;./libs/commons-logging-1.1.jar;./jmasslogpro.jar com.mlp.syslogd.SyslogD

There is also syslog message generation available: java -classpath ./libs/OROMatcher1.0.jar;./libs/jppf-client.jar;./libs/jppf-common.jar;./libs/jppf-common-node.jar;./libs/commons-logging-1.1.jar;./jmasslogpro.jar com.mlp.syslog.SyslogSend -host yourhost


More information avaible on wiki. Happy hacking!

